\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs28\b0 He sat at his computer, staring at the unresponded message he had sent a week ago. A sinking feeling gnawed at his chest, pulling him into a state of unease. }{\f0\fs28\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::0>Why hasn't she responded?<!$Scr_Cs::0>}{\f0\fs28\b0\i1  }{\f0\fs28\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::0>We used to talk every day, and now she's gone silent. <!$Scr_Cs::0>}{\f0\fs28\b0 Memories of laughter, shared secrets, and warm friendship flickered through his mind, contrasting sharply with the cold emptiness of the screen. He tried to brush off the thought that something might've happened to her, but it kept creeping back, intertwining with a more unsettling fear. }{\f0\fs28\i1\cf4 <$Scr_Cs::0>Maybe she doesn't want to talk to me anymore. Maybe our friendship has faded into the past, and I'm the only one clinging to it.<!$Scr_Cs::0>}{\f0\fs28\b0  The cursor blinked, like a taunting reminder of their growing distance, and he felt lost, adrift in the silence that had settled between them.}{ }
